com.opengamma.strata.market.surface

Interface Surface

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    NodalSurface
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstantNodalSurface, InterpolatedNodalSurface

    public interface Surface
    A surface that maps a double x-value and y-value to a double z-value.

    Implementations of this interface provide the ability to find a z-value on the surface from the x-value and y-value.

    Each implementation will be backed by a number of parameters. The meaning of the parameters is implementation dependent. The sensitivity of the result to each of the parameters can also be obtained.

    See Also:
    InterpolatedNodalSurface

    • Method Detail

      • getMetadata

        SurfaceMetadata getMetadata()
        Gets the surface metadata.

        This method returns metadata about the surface and the surface parameters.

        The metadata includes an optional list of parameter metadata. If parameter metadata is present, the size of the list will match the number of parameters of this surface.

        Returns:
        the metadata

        Returns:

      • zValueParameterSensitivity

        SurfaceUnitParameterSensitivity zValueParameterSensitivity(double x,
                                                           double y)
        Computes the sensitivity of the z-value with respect to the surface parameters.

        This returns an array with one element for each x-y parameter of the surface. The array contains one a sensitivity value for each parameter used to create the surface.

        Parameters:
        x - the x-value at which the parameter sensitivity is computed
        y - the y-value at which the parameter sensitivity is computed
        Returns:
        the sensitivity at the x/y/ point
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if the sensitivity cannot be calculated

      • toNodalSurface

        default NodalSurface toNodalSurface()
        Concerts this surface to a nodal surface.

        A nodal surface is based on specific x-y-z values, typically with interpolation. See InterpolatedNodalSurface for more details.
